name: invalid_utf16_lone_low_surrogate
description: |
  An ASCII 'A' (0x0041) followed by a lone low surrogate (0xDC00) in
  little-endian UTF-16. A low surrogate must be preceded by a high surrogate
  in the range 0xD800..=0xDBFF; on its own it is not a valid Unicode scalar
  value and well-formed UTF-16 decoders must reject it.

  This complements the existing lone-high-surrogate case, since accepting an
  unpaired low surrogate is a distinct validation failure.

  See the Unicode UTF-16 conformance rules (D91, well-formed UTF-16):
  https://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode15.0.0/ch03.pdf
format: hex
decode-as: bytes
invalid-as: utf16-le
tags:
  - "encoding"
  - "unicode"
  - "utf16"
  - "invalid-utf16"
  - "surrogate"
  - "lone-surrogate"
  - "low-surrogate"
---
41 00 00 dc   # 'A' then lone low surrogate U+DC00
